  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (ccdfd3a 2022-04-27T00:10:52.272849264+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe contents of events containing `int` types are shown in the traces with an off-by-one value.\r\n\r\nAs an example:\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport \"ds-test/test.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract Foo is DSTest {\r\n\r\n    event custom_int_event(int256);\r\n\r\n    function setUp() public {}\r\n\r\n    function testExample() public {\r\n\r\n        for (int i=-2; i <= 2; i++) {\r\n            emit log_int(i);\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        emit custom_int_event(-1);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nRunning this test with `forge test -vvvvv` results in the following trace:\r\n\r\n```\r\nRunning 1 test for test/foo.sol:Foo\r\n[PASS] testExample() (gas: 7091)\r\nLogs:\r\n  -2\r\n  -1\r\n  0\r\n  1\r\n  2\r\n\r\nTraces:\r\n  [98] Foo::setUp() \r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n\r\n  [7091] Foo::testExample() \r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: -3)\r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: -2)\r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: 0)\r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: 1)\r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: 2)\r\n    ├─ emit custom_int_event(: -2)\r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n\r\nTest result: ok. 1 passed; 0 failed; finished in 295.68µs\r\n```",
