    "body": "To reproduce, you should enable verbosity level at least 4 since the incorrect printing of the int type(s) happens in the trace, and this is not a failing test. I tried with the latest version, and it's still printing `-n` as `-(n+1)` in the traces:\r\n```\r\nforge test -vvvv\r\n[⠊] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\n\r\nRunning 1 test for test/Contract.t.sol:ContractTest\r\n[PASS] testExample() (gas: 190)\r\nTraces:\r\n  [190] ContractTest::testExample() \r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n\r\nTest result: ok. 1 passed; 0 failed; finished in 267.06µs\r\n\r\nRunning 1 test for test/foo.sol:Foo\r\n[PASS] testExample() (gas: 7091)\r\nLogs:\r\n  -2\r\n  -1\r\n  0\r\n  1\r\n  2\r\n\r\nTraces:\r\n  [7091] Foo::testExample() \r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: -3)\r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: -2)\r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: 0)\r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: 1)\r\n    ├─ emit log_int(: 2)\r\n    ├─ emit custom_int_event(: -2)\r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n\r\nforge --version\r\nforge 0.2.0 (a97090d 2022-05-01T00:04:17.612524414+00:00)\r\n```\r\n",
